were unathorized 
during a weekend campaign swing through several western states 
dukakis responded tersely when asked if jackson would have veto 
power over his decision he said the decision was his alone to make 
dukakis is to travel tuesday night to washington where he is 
scheduled to hold a series of capitol hill meetings on wednesday 
and also address the annual convention of the naacp 
when he arrives back in boston on wednesday night dukakis will 
have two work days left to make good on his promise to resolve the 
states budget problems by the end of the week 
on his desk is an 1175 billion spending plan for fiscal 1989 
which began july 1 legislative leaders have urged dukakis to use 
his lineitem veto power to reduce that spending plan dukakis also 
is awaiting legislative passage of a politically sensitive plan to 
eliminate the 370 million deficit remaining from fiscal 1988 
the governor is scheduled to take saturday off and fly to 
atlanta for the convention on sunday 
