the following are excerpts translated from 
russian by the official soviet news agency tass of soviet leader 
mikhail s gorbachevs speech monday to the polish parliament the 
sejm in warsaw 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
on sovietpolish relations 
there is still much in sovietpolish relations that does not 
meet the needs of both sides 
this applies to direct human contacts as well new crossings 
will be set up on the sovietpolish border the possibilities of 
contacts across the border will be expanded and more railway and 
air lines will connect our countries the idea of establishing a 
ferry between szscecin and leningrad is being discussed 
our joint history is a rich fullblooded history of two 
neighboring peoples we have causes for pride but there are 
things that have to be revealed and shown more fully 
this history also has its complexities what is called blank 
spots notions that are based more on emotions rather than on 
strict scientific knowledge form at times around them 
there is only one road to the truth here study of facts calm 
comparison of viewpoints and scientific discussions 
history cannot be replayed but lessons can and should be drawn 
from it 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
on the eastwest ideology battle 
it is very important in these conditions to clear the 
ideological struggle of foul play psychological warfare and 
cultivation of mistrust among nations are incompatible with the 
norms of civilized statetostate contacts 
it is essential to do away with the preaching of militarism 
hatred and enmity so that differences between countries become a 
stimulus for cooperation rather than a hindrance to it 
the nations need the truth about one another western society 
has a poor knowledge of realities in the socialist world it has 
been hammered into peoples heads there since they were in diapers 
that the communists are the bad guys who have enslaved their 
peoples and are sharpening their knives against the free nations of 
the west 
we have to abandon our own simplistic approaches in presenting 
western realities as well 
it is imperative to see all the diversity the complexity and 
equivocality the contradictoriness of what is happening in western 
countries in economic political social and other spheres 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
on conventional arms 
as far as the governments of nato countries are concerned they 
traditionally look at conventional arms as a legitimate component 
of power politics and uphold the nuclear deterence concept while 
paying lip service to the need to reduce conventional arms they 
continue in fact building up their military resources 
we would for instance be prepared to withdraw our matching 
aircraft from forwarddeployment sites in eastern europe if nato 
agrees not to base its 72 f16 fighterbombers rejected by spain 
in italy 
the time has come for deeper troops and arms cuts in europe and 
this requires expediting work in vienna to hammer out a mandate for 
opening negotiations both on the reduction of conventional forces 
and armaments and on confidencebuilding measures on a europewide 
scale 
we suggest effecting the cuts in three phases 
at the first phase all the imbalances and asymmetries between 
nato and the warsaw treaty as regards both troop strength and 
primary arms are to be identified and eliminated this approach 
could be applied both to the entire european continent as a whole 
and to its individual regions for example central europe southern 
europe etc 
for identifying the imbalances and asymmetries we suggest 
exchanging initial data even before the talks or simultaneously 
with their commencement in amounts to be dictated by the agreed 
subject of the negotiations 
careful checks on the data including onsite inspections are 
to be run soon after the start of the talks so as to avoid a 
repetition of the sad experience of the debates on numbers that 
once deadlocked the vienna talks on central europe 
let me note in passing that if nato shows readiness we can 
discuss the issue of the imbalances and asymmetries even before the 
start of the formal talks in connection with the exchanges of data 
on troops and weaponry 
at the second phase the nato and warsaw treaty forces are to be 
reduced by 500000 men on each side from the levels existing after 
the elimination of the imbalances and asymmetries the cuts are to 
be carried out by disbanding military units along with elimination 
of their organic arms 
at the third phase the cuts are to be continued so as to 
finally lend the military units of both military alliances a purely 
defensive nature 
all the reduction phases would provide for effective 
verificaiton arrangements including onsite inspections 
i would like to add to this that we are prepared not only at the 
third phase but also from the very start of the cuts to come to 
terms on the priority reduction of tactical nuclear weapons 
tactical strike aircraft and tanks 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

