rejected the resolution sunday when some delegates claimed the 
boycott would hurt us businesses but the deputies reversed their 
vote monday to express solidarity with anglican archbishop desmond 
tutu of south africa who has promoted the boycott as a means of 
protesting racial segregation in that nation 
