<TEXT>
mikhail s gorbachev and wojciech 
jaruzelski speaking of painful episodes in their countries shared 
history say no one should shirk from examining the past honestly 
but the soviet and polish communist leaders stopped short monday 
of uttering the one word that symbolizes the most painful episode 
in polishsoviet relations and the one historical blank spot 
most poles want explicated 
neither said katyn the name of the forest in the soviet 
union where the bodies of about 4300 polish army officers were 
uncovered by nazi troops during world war ii 
each of the officers representing the cream of polish society 
was bound and shot with a single bullet to the base of the skull 
official soviet and polish histories have long maintained that 
the officers were killed by the nazis in 1941 but independent 
historians and most poles believe they were killed in 1940 on the 
orders of josef stalin by the nkvd secret police predecessor of 
the kgb 
a joint sovietpolish historical commission was charged last 
year with investigating the katyn massacre and other painful 
blank spots including the 1920 war between poland and the 
soviet union and stalins murder of virtually all leading members 
