benjamin benny begin brings the looks and 
mannerisms of his father former prime minister menachem begin to 
his run for parliament and the nostalgia factor could be important 
for both him and his party 
benny begin a 45yearold government geologist is the first 
son of an israeli prime minister to run for office he was chosen 
this month as a candidate of the likud bloc the rightwing 
alliance his father founded in the nov 1 elections 
he is taller and leaner but the hand and facial gestures some 
of his rhetorical flourishes and even his tone of voice are almost 
identical to his fathers 
party officials believe the begin name on likuds list could 
help it win what promises to be a close contest with the 
centerleft labor party of foreign minister shimon peres for 
control of the knesset the 120seat parliament 
in an interview with the associated press benny begin insisted 
he cannot fill his fathers shoes 
it is unreasonable to hang hopes on me because my name is 
begin he said people like him are born very rarely 
begin said he sees little chance for territorial compromise or a 
peace agreement with neighboring jordan so believes like his 
father that israel should keep control of the occupied west bank 
and gaza strip 
i am not a prophet of doom he said with a smile i look 
at all the alternatives and seek the lesser evil the one that 
doesnt endanger israels survival which means maintaining 
absolute israeli control over the land of israel west of the jordan 
river 
menachem begin 74 was born in poland his mix of charm and 
fiery rhetoric proved a winning formula for ending three decades of 
labor party government in 1977 
in 1978 he shared the nobel peace prize with the late egyptian 
president anwar sadat for the process leading to their peace treaty 
the next year then resigned suddenly in 1983 and has been a 
recluse since 
associates and friends said begin resigned because he was 
depressed about israels loss of more than 650 soldiers in the 
invasion of lebanon which began under his leadership in 1982 
