two us helicopters traded fire with a 
pair of iranian gunboats after the boats attacked a tanker in the 
northern persian gulf today us military sources said 
the sources who spoke on condition of anonymity said there was 
no damage to the aircraft and it was not known whether the boats 
were damaged in the clash which took place at about 7 pm 
the sources said the helicopters off the us missile frigate 
nicholas were responding to a distress call from a panamanianflag 
tanker west of irans farsi island 
the helicopters took fire from the two small boats and 
returned fire with rockets said a us official there was no 
damage to the helos helicopters we have no damage assessment on 
the boats 
