mrs oakley said reducing forces in europe was a subject for 
consideration by the 16member nato alliance and not for the united 
states and the soviet union to decide on their own 
gorbachev made the two proposals monday in a speech to the 
polish parliament in warsaw the swift us response reflected an 
unwillingness to explore new approaches with moscow in preference 
to ongoing multinational negotiations in vienna and proposed 
bloctobloc talks 
we see little utility in proposing a new different form 
mrs oakley said 
the vienna negotiations have not produced troop reductions new 
negotiations are supposed to be held between the north atlantic 
treaty organization and the warsaw pact in the austrian capital 
but a date has not been set 
the key problem appears to be a us demand that the soviet 
union simultaneously considers improving its human rights record 
mrs oakley reading from a prepared statement said vast 
conventional superiority of the warsaw pact over nato was the 
cause of security problems in europe 
the first step toward rectifying this imbalance is to reach 
eastwest agreement on a negotiating mandate for new arms control 
talks covering nato and warsaw pact conventional forces from the 
atlantic to the ural mountains she said 
mr gorbachevs proposal is an attempt to divert attention 
from the business at hand in vienna if the soviet union is sincere 
in its pursuit of conventional reductions it will work in vienna to 
achieve a muitally acceptable mandate and a balanced outcome 
at the same time the state department spokeswoman criticized 
gorbachevs suggestion that the warsaw pact would consider 
withdrawing analogus air force units from eeastern europe if 
nato aggreed to drop plans to move 72 us f16 warplanes to italy 
from spain where they were ordered to leave over three years 
a matter of common alliance concern will not be undertaken on 
a bilateral basis mrs oakley said we are prepared to give 
serious consideration to any proposal that will enhance the common 
goal of enhancing stability in europe 
she drew attention to a statement by manfred woerner of west 
germany the new secretary general of nat0 rejecting the proposal 
he said the nato alliance was concerned mostly with reducing land 
forces on their own aircraft do not capture and hold 
territory 
