<TEXT>
former white house aide michael k deaver was 
ordered tuesday to appear sept 23 to be sentenced for lying to a 
grand jury and a house subcommittee about his lobbying business 
us district judge thomas penfield jackson also scheduled a 
sept 15 hearing to take testimony about deavers problems with 
alcohol which the defense contended impaired the former 
presidential aides memory he gave sworn testimony two years ago 
testimony about deavers alcoholism would be offered by the 
defense in an attempt to show there were mitigating circumstances 
that would warrant a short sentence or probation 
the hearing promises to be the first full airing of the 
alcoholism issue which was never raised during the trial because 
deavers lawyers rested their case without calling any witnesses 
a recovering alcoholic deaver was convicted dec 16 1987 on 
three counts of lying to a grand jury and a house subcommitee about 
the lobbying business he formed in 1985 after resigning as 
president reagans deputy chief of staff 
deaver who was questioned by the panels about allegations that 
his lobbying of former government colleagues violated federal 
conflictofinterest laws could be sentenced up to five years in 
prison for each of the perjury convictions 
the sentencing was stayed on feb 2 after a federal appeals 
court struck down the independent counsel law under which deaver 
was prosecuted 
the supreme courts 71 decision last month upholding the 
constitutionality of courtappointed independent counsels set the 
stage for deaver to be sentenced 
during a brief hearing on the case stephen braga one of 
deavers lawyers told jackson that the defense wanted to present 
testimony from the head of an alcoholism rehabilitation clinic in 
havre de grace md where deaver spent 30 days in 1985 
braga said deavers doctor at georgetown university hospital 
would also be called to testify about the former presidential 
aides treatment for the disease earlier that year 
the defense has contended in court papers that deavers memory 
was impaired by his bout with alcoholism and therefore he wasnt 
lying when he testified that he couldnt recall making certain 
lobbying contacts 
during the trial deavers lawyers rested their case without 
presenting witnesses including doctors who treated him for 
alcoholism 
several former employees of michael k deaver amp associates who 
appeared as prosecution witnesses testified during 
crossexamination that deaver suffered memory lapses and moodiness 
which they later attributed to alcoholism 
but the judge instructed jurors to disregard this testimony 
saying it was speculative and selfserving 
independent counsel whitney north seymour jr told the judge he 
might call a medical expert to rebut testimony given by deavers 
witnesses 
deavers hospitalization for alcoholism in june 1985 is a 
period cited by the defense as a time when his memory was impaired 
by alcoholic withdrawal and sedation 
several telephone calls deaver made to government officials 
including one to thentransportation secretary elizabeth dole took 
place while the former white house aide was in the hospital 
deaver was found guilty of lying to the grand jury when he 
testified i dont recall any government contact i made on 
behalf of trans world airlines 
