<TEXT>
although he may lose the election opposition 
candidate cuauhtemoc cardenas appears to have secured a position as 
the rallying point for the discontent with the party that has ruled 
mexico for 59 years 
whether he won the presidential election or not is still a 
matter of heated debate he says he did the governing 
institutional revolutionary party or pri says he didnt 
privately top pri officials admit cardenas won the federal 
district the core of the sprawling mexico city metropolitan area 
and three of mexicos 31 states 
even those victories would be a stunning blow to the pri which 
has won every presidential race since its founding in 1929 with at 
least 70 percent of the vote and never has lost a senate or 
gubernatorial race 
cardenas claimed monday he won 39 percent of the vote nationwide 
to pri candidate carlos salinas de gortaris 35 percent 
after a weeks delay and opposition charges of fraud the 
government has only provided partial returns on the race for the 
lower house of congress 
figures released tuesday by the pri say salinas had 5359 
percent of the votes counted cardenas was second with 2608 
percent and manuel j clouthier of the conservative national 
action party followed with 1604 percent 
even these figures which the opposition disputes would be an 
astonishing feat for cardenas a candidate who in december started 
to build his predominantly leftist coalition from a tiny base 
his campaign was considered unlikely to shake the foundations of 
power and ruling politicians dismissed him as a candidate of 
nostalgia who was trading on his famous name 
through it all the charismatic candidate never lost his 
composure 
before hundreds of thousands of adoring supporters on the 
campaign trail in the steamy battle over vote fraud at 
middleofthenight news conferences in the dayslong wait for the 
returns he was always calm always reasonable 
while clouthier barreled down the campaign trail blustering 
about civil disobedience cardenas quietly counseled restraint and 
spoke of using the force of law 
cardenas 54 spent the day before the election in the central 
state of michoacan where he once was the governing pris governor 
he wasnt basking in the warmth accorded a favorite son he was 
