<TEXT>
legislators of a mountain enclave that has been 
involved in an ethnic tugofwar for months voted tuesday to secede 
from azerbaijan and join armenia a dramatic first in soviet 
politics but probably futile 
the legislature of nagornokarabakh a predominantly armenian 
enclave in azerbaijan was unanimous except for one abstention in 
the decision to secede and rename the area the artsakh autonomous 
region of armenia radio reporters in the territory reported 
about 160000 people live in nagornokarabakh and threequarters 
are ethnic armenians 
dissident historian roy medvedev said the legislative action 
appears to have little chance of success 
its unconstitutional he said it cannot be considered 
legal 
never before in soviet history has a regions legislature voted 
to withdraw from the republic of which it is a part he said 
the decision defies central authorities all the way up to 
mikhail s gorbachev and tests kremlin tolerance of assertions of 
rights by the countrys more than 100 national groups gorbachev 
has encouraged citizens to speak out under his policy of glasnost 
or openness 
the soviet constitution gives citizens the right to 
selfdetermination but also requires that a republic consent to 
any change in its boundaries 
nagornokarabakh is an autonomous region of azerbaijan which is 
soviet armenias neighbor in the caucasus 
its legislature asked feb 20 that the azerbaijani and armenian 
governments approve the transfer to armenia the armenians agreed 
june 15 but azerbaijans legislature rejected the request two days 
later 
strikes and street rallies have disrupted stepanakert the 
territorial capital for weeks 
a statement by the legislature read over the telephone by 
reporters for the stepanakert radio station said the soviet of 
peoples deputies of the nagornokarabakh autonomous region 
declares its secession from the azerbaijan soviet socialist 
republic 
armenians most of whom are christians consider 
nagornokarabakh part of their ancestral homeland but in 1923 the 
region was assigned to azerbaijan which is predominantly moslem 
the dispute began with demonstrations by armenians in both 
nagornokarabakh and armenia itself in february and ethnic riots 
were reported in sumgait an azerbaijan port officials said 32 
people were killed 26 armenians and six azerbaijanis and 200 
injured 
gorbachev told a national communist party conference june 28 the 
powers of the countrys 15 republics and other ethnic entities 
should be expanded but said some ethnic minorities were going too 
far 
some think that any questions from the redrawing of borders 
to the establishment of opposition parties can be resolved 
through glasnost gorbachev said 
the central committee believes such abuses of democratization 
run counter to the task of perestroika contradict the peoples 
interests he said perestroika or restructuring is what 
gorbachev calls his plans for social and economic reform 
communist party officials in moscow rejected the territorial 
demand in february but said living conditions in nagornokarabakh 
would be improved 
the kremlin approved a multimilliondollar package of social and 
cultural improvements for the region in march but strikes and 
demonstrations continued 
after azerbaijan rejected the transfer request 
nagornokarabakhs legislature proposed a compromise putting the 
region under temporary control of the central government in moscow 
armenian delegates to the party conference in moscow suggested 
other compromises that included attaching the region to stavropol 
gorbachevs home district in the russian republic 
azerbaijans leaders did not budge 
medvedev said in a telephone interview that tuesdays decision 
appeared aimed at pressuring moscow into approving the territorial 
transfer 
pravda the communist party newspaper said on tuesday an 
overwhelming majority of armenians who began a strike july 4 in 
yerevan the armenian capital had decided to return to work 
dissident journalist mofses gorgisyan said the walkout was 
gaining strength however and that representatives of factories in 
the republic of 34 million people reported 70 percent absenteeism 
monday 
he said by telephone from yerevan that soldiers and tanks were 
deployed around the citys outskirts and militiamen patrolled 
inside the city limits 
the central committee of armenias communist party criticized 
officials throughout the republic tuesday for delaying showing 
carelessness and irresponsibility in the realization of practical 
measures aimed at improving the situation the government 
newspaper izvestia reported 
gorgisyan said 300000 to 400000 people gathered outside 
armenias institute of ancient manuscripts known as the 
matenadaran on monday night to support the strike and press the 
territorial demand a reporter for the republics official news 
agency armenpress said the number was about 100000 
gorgisyan 27 belongs to an underground group called the 
alliance for national selfdetermination and publishes an 
underground journal called fatherland 
</TEXT>
