a boy trapped for 20 hours under the 
rubble of a collapsed department store may lose use of his kidneys 
doctors said 
university of texas medical branch physicians treating 
9yearold jorge mena of merida mexico said toxins from dead 
muscle tissue apparently destroyed his bodys ability to cleanse 
his blood 
however doctors said jorges spunk may help him through the 
critical first days of what may be a monthslong stay at the 
hospital 
hes mad and hes scared said jason calhoun an orthopedic 
surgeon 
mena and a cousin who lost a leg in the accident in brownsville 
last week are receiving highpressure oxygen treatments both are 
in critical condition officials said 
he complains the whole time he is in the hyperbaric 
chamber said dr john mader who is overseeing menas treatment 
at utmbs marine biomedical institute 
but thats good mader said because hes a fighter and 
that is what it takes 
jorges mother remained hospitalized in brownsville and a 
15yearold sister mya died in the accident authorities said 
the boys father who like his son speaks no english lies outside 
the chamber window so he can look at the boy 
