usx spokesman george kuebler harvest time is still down the road 
for a lot of crops yet so we dont see any impact 
an inland newsletter said the company anticipates some customers 
might cut back on orders if the drought continues 
farm equipment manufacturers in particular may be hurt by 
declining sales of tractors and combines the newsletter said 
inland spokesman george nekvasil said some companies that depend 
on river traffic stalled by droughtlowered waters may reduce steel 
